abstract: South Korean swimmer Park Tae-hwan is barred for 18 months following positive result for testosterone in an out-of-competition drug test.
lead_paragraph: Park Tae-hwan, who won the 400-meter freestyle at the 2008 Beijing Olympics, was barred for 18 months because of a positive result for testosterone.

headline.print_headline: Sports Briefing | Swimming; Test Bars South Korean
